# Development Environment Variables
#
# IMPORTANT: Copy this file to .dev.vars and fill in real values
#   cp .dev.vars.example .dev.vars
#
# NEVER commit .dev.vars (it's in .gitignore)
#
# These variables are automatically loaded by Cloudflare Workers in development.
# For production, use: wrangler secret put SECRET_NAME

# ============================================================================
# WORKOS AUTHENTICATION (REQUIRED)
# ============================================================================
# Get these from: https://dashboard.workos.com/
# 1. Go to WorkOS Dashboard
# 2. Select your project
# 3. Navigate to API Keys section

# WorkOS Client ID (public identifier, starts with client_)
WORKOS_CLIENT_ID=client_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# WorkOS API Key (secret, starts with sk_)
WORKOS_API_KEY=sk_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ============================================================================
# APIFY INTEGRATION (REQUIRED for Apify-based MCP servers)
# ============================================================================
# Get from: https://console.apify.com/account/integrations
# 1. Log in to Apify Console
# 2. Go to Settings → Integrations
# 3. Copy your API token (starts with apify_api_)

# Apify API Token (40 characters)
APIFY_API_TOKEN=apify_api_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

# ============================================================================
# AI GATEWAY (Optional - for rate limiting and caching)
# ============================================================================
# Get from Cloudflare Dashboard:
# 1. Go to AI → AI Gateway
# 2. Create a new gateway or select existing
# 3. Copy Gateway ID and API token

# AI Gateway ID (if using Cloudflare AI Gateway)
# AI_GATEWAY_ID=your-gateway-id

# AI Gateway Token (if required)
# AI_GATEWAY_TOKEN=your-gateway-token

# ============================================================================
# CUSTOM ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# ============================================================================
# Add any additional secrets your server needs below
# Examples:
# EXTERNAL_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
# EXTERNAL_API_URL=https://api.example.com

# ============================================================================
# NOTES
# ============================================================================
# - All secrets above are required for local development
# - For production deployment, use: wrangler secret put SECRET_NAME
# - Example: echo "real_token" | wrangler secret put APIFY_API_TOKEN
# - Never hardcode these values in source code
# - Resource IDs (D1, KV, R2) are configured in wrangler.jsonc, not here
